# Code guide: Objective-C

---

## Overview

**Guide quality: 3/5** — One authoritative source (Google ObjC) merged; consensus and per-source rules derived from it. Trustworthiness high for that source; completeness will improve when NYTimes/Goat/others are merged. Re-score after adding sources or resolving conflicts.

Objective-C is a dynamic, object-oriented extension of C and the historical primary language for Apple platforms (iOS, macOS, tvOS, watchOS). **Best for:** maintaining legacy Apple apps, frameworks that must support ObjC callers, mixed ObjC/Swift codebases, and Cocoa/CocoaTouch APIs. **Avoid for:** new greenfield Apple-only projects (prefer Swift), performance-critical or cross-platform code where Swift or C++ is a better fit. **Ecosystem:** Clang/LLVM, Xcode, CocoaPods/Carthage/SPM; [Apple Cocoa Coding Guidelines](https://developer.apple.com/library/archive/documentation/Cocoa/Conceptual/CodingGuidelines/). Style guide last updated: 2026-03-03.

